description:
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to be looking for a systemic psychotherapy research supervisor and teacher with a research and publications record to contribute to the research teaching and research supervision on the thriving Professional Doctorate in Systemic Psychotherapy including a part of the Tavistock Integrated Doctoral Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join and develop this interesting and expanding doctoral programme set up to enable family therapists / systemic psychotherapists to carry out innovative clinical research to make a contribution to the systemic field. The programme offers learning from diverse cultural, historical and methodological sources and perspectives and we are looking for a teacher and supervisor who is able to embrace this with confidence and enthusiasm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide joint leadership and to contribute to the continued development of the Systemic Doctorate programme and its administration and contribute research teaching and supervision of Doctorate projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Esther Usiskin Cohen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Systemic Training Portfolio Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email :ecohen2@tavi-port.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
